{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A plugin whose manifest is missing a required field is rejected before any code from that plugin is executed.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"This is primarily a loader handoff behavior (manifest validation must gate module import/execution). Unit tests of the validator alone can miss a wiring bug where import happens too early. Integration is sufficient because the behavior can be proven with in-process modules plus a temp plugin directory; no real HTTP, subprocess, or external API is required, and no AI/ML output is involved.","test_description":"Create a temp plugin directory with one plugin whose manifest omits a required field and whose entry module would create a sentinel side effect if executed (e.g., set a shared flag or write a temp file). Run the real loader pipeline (discover -> validate -> resolve -> initialize). Assert: loader reports manifest rejection; sentinel side effect is absent; `onLoad` was never called.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.16,"Integration":0.79,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When plugin A declares a dependency on plugin B, plugin B's `onLoad` hook is called before plugin A's.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure mode is cross-module orchestration (dependency graph resolution + lifecycle dispatcher ordering). Unit tests for topological sort or hook runner in isolation can miss integration ordering mistakes. Integration test with real loader wiring and local plugin fixtures captures this without requiring external infrastructure.","test_description":"Build fixture plugins A and B where A depends on B; each `onLoad` appends its name to a shared in-memory log. Execute loader end-to-end over fixture directory. Assert load log order is `[B, A]` and both hooks run exactly once.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.84,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When two plugins each declare a dependency on the other, the loader reports the cycle and loads neither.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"Cycle detection plus suppression of initialization is a multi-module interaction (resolver + initializer). A pure unit test of cycle detection may not prove that initialization is blocked. Integration is enough with local fixtures; no real network/OS-subprocess dependency and no model output dependence.","test_description":"Create plugins A and B with mutual dependencies. Run loader pipeline on fixture directory. Assert: cycle error is reported with involved plugin names; neither entry module side effect occurs; neither `onLoad` hook is invoked.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.14,"Integration":0.82,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A plugin's `onLoad` hook is only invoked after the plugin's entry module has been imported and executed.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"This behavior is about sequencing between module import execution and lifecycle invocation across loader components. Unit tests of hook invocation or importer alone can miss ordering regressions. Integration with real Node import of local fixtures provides the needed signal; no external boundary requires System.","test_description":"Use a fixture plugin whose entry module sets `initialized=true` as a top-level side effect and whose `onLoad` asserts/records that `initialized` is already true. Run loader. Assert `onLoad` ran and observed post-import state; fail if `onLoad` runs before module execution.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When a plugin throws an error during its `onLoad` hook, the loader continues initializing the remaining plugins that do not depend on it.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"This is fault-isolation and dependency-aware continuation across multiple plugins (error handling + dependency filtering + scheduler). Unit tests of error handling alone can miss real orchestration behavior. Integration with fixture plugins is sufficient; no real subprocess/network and no AI/ML dependency.","test_description":"Create three plugins: `Bad` throws in `onLoad`, `Independent` has no dependency on `Bad`, and `Dependent` depends on `Bad`. Run loader. Assert: error for `Bad` is recorded; `Independent.onLoad` still executes; `Dependent.onLoad` is skipped/blocked according to dependency rules.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.13,"Integration":0.83,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]}
